#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.114"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.114:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.114:0.2"
msgid "12. Andhakavindavagga "
msgstr "12. At Andhakavinda "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.114:0.3"
msgid "114. Andhakavindasutta "
msgstr "114. At Andhakavinda "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an5.114:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā magadhesu viharati andhakavinde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Magadhans at Andhakavinda. "

msgctxt "an5.114:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: samādapetabbā → samādāpetabbā (?)
msgctxt "an5.114:2.1"
msgid "“Ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, te vo, ānanda, bhikkhū pañcasu dhammesu samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, those mendicants who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training should be encouraged, supported, and established in five things. "

msgctxt "an5.114:2.2"
msgid "Katamesu pañcasu? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.114:2.3"
msgid "‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, sīlavā hotha, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvutā viharatha ācāragocarasampannā aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvino, samādāya sikkhatha sikkhāpadesū’ti—iti pātimokkhasaṃvare samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "They should be encouraged, supported, and established in restraint in the monastic code: ‘Reverends, please be ethical. Live restrained in the code of conduct, conducting yourselves well and seeking alms in suitable places. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, keep the rules you’ve undertaken.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: nipakkasatino → nepakkasatino (?)
msgctxt "an5.114:3.1"
msgid "‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, indriyesu guttadvārā viharatha ārakkhasatino nipakkasatino, sārakkhitamānasā satārakkhena cetasā samannāgatā’ti—iti indriyasaṃvare samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "They should be encouraged, supported, and established in sense restraint: ‘Reverends, please live with sense doors guarded, mindfully alert and on guard, with protected mind, having a heart protected by mindfulness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.114:4.1"
msgid "‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, appabhassā hotha, bhasse pariyantakārino’ti—iti bhassapariyante samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "They should be encouraged, supported, and established in limiting their speech: ‘Reverends, please speak little. Put a limit on your speech.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an5.114:5.1"
msgid "‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, āraññikā hotha, araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevathā’ti—iti kāyavūpakāse samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "They should be encouraged, supported, and established in retreat: ‘Reverends, please live in the wilderness. Frequent remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.139, sc6
msgctxt "an5.114:6.1"
msgid "‘Etha tumhe, āvuso, sammādiṭṭhikā hotha sammādassanena samannāgatā’ti—iti sammādassane samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā. "
msgstr "They should be encouraged, supported, and established in right perspective: ‘Reverends, please hold right view and have right perspective.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.114:6.2"
msgid "Ye te, ānanda, bhikkhū navā acirapabbajitā adhunāgatā imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ, te vo, ānanda, bhikkhū imesu pañcasu dhammesu samādapetabbā nivesetabbā patiṭṭhāpetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "Those mendicants who are junior, recently gone forth, newly come to this teaching and training should be encouraged, supported, and established in these five things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.114:6.3"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

